# Lock files compiled by `gh aw` (https://github.com/github/gh-aw).
# `linguist-generated` hides them from default diffs and PR file views.
# `merge=ours` keeps the local copy on merge conflicts; it relies on the
# built-in "ours" merge driver, which must be enabled per-clone with:
#   git config merge.ours.driver true
# Without that one-time config the attribute is a no-op (safe), so a
# missing driver only means conflicts on this file fall back to the
# normal 3-way merge. Recompile with `gh aw compile <workflow>` after
# any merge that touches the source `.md`.
.github/workflows/*.lock.yml linguist-generated=true merge=ours
